        <item>
          <actionDate>2018-05-15</actionDate>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2019-08-16T18:45:46Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Using Data to Prevent Opioid Diversion Act of 2018</b></p> <p>This bill establishes a new requirement intended to help drug manufacturers and distributors identify and prevent suspicious orders of opioids and reduce rates of diversion.</p> <p>Specifically, the Drug Enforcement Administration must to use its automated data system&#8212;the Automated Reports and Consolidated Ordering System&#8212;to inform drug manufacturers and distributors about the quantity and type of opioids that are distributed to pharmacies and practitioners.</p>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2018-05-15T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
